<item>
            <title>[SPARK-14676] Catch, wrap, and re-throw exceptions from Await.result in order to capture full stacktrace</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-14676</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When &lt;tt&gt;Await.result&lt;/tt&gt; throws an exception which originated from a different thread, the resulting stacktrace doesn&apos;t include the path leading to the &lt;tt&gt;Await.result()&lt;/tt&gt; call itself, making it difficult to identify the impact of these exceptions. For example, I&apos;ve seen cases where broadcast cleaning errors propagate to the main thread and crash it but the resulting stacktrace doesn&apos;t include any of the main thread&apos;s code, making it difficult to pinpoint which exception crashed that thread. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
